p2215
tp2216
a(I0
VThe better approach: Narrow the focus to hone into one aspect, or a few major moments, of the person\u2019s life.
p2217
tp2218
a(I0
VLincoln, for instance, eschews the retelling of the president\u2019s rise, opting instead to reflect his character through the single storyline of the congressional fight to end slavery.
p2219
tp2220
a(I0
V3.
p2221
tp2222
a(I0
VDon\u2019t fall in love with your own star.
p2223
tp2224
a(I0
VIt may be the biggest saving grace of Get On Up: the fact that Boseman is a more than capable Brown imitator, embodying his tics, his growl, his bouffant hair, that regal chin, his assuredness in his body\u2019s electric motions, his supreme swagger.
p2225
tp2226
a(I0
